fields.value:
CI's:
BRXNY-EDGE-FW1
BRXNY-EDGE-FW2
BRXNY-EDGE-FW1/02 Firewall Pair upgrade to 9.1.8;9.1.8
Devices in question are listed below;
BRXNY-EDGE-FW1
BRXNY-EDGE-FW2

BRXNY-EDGE-FW Pair is running 8.1.15-h3 PAN OS version which is no longer supported by Palo Alto. This update moves us to the recommended version within the 9.1.x software line. 9.1.8 is a recommended and stable panos release already running on other maximus firewalls.

BRXNY-EDGE-FW upgrade path:
Follow Palo Alto recommended process for each version upgrade below, performing each step for both cluster members and testing stability before beginning the next stage of the upgrade.

8.1.15 -h3 -- Current Version
9.1.x - Transition Version
9.1.8 - Intended Version

fields.name: BackOutPlan
fields.value:
In the event of any upgrade issues with one member of the firewall cluster, cease all upgrade efforts on the second member and leave that member as our operational firewall; troubleshoot and resolve issues on the affected member up to and including rollback to the most recent successful version.
Current version - 8.1.15 -h3

fields.name: RiskComments
fields.value:
Previously performed on multiple other Maximus Firewalls without issue or outage. Low risk to business operations due to redundant paired firewall; slight risk of needing to operate without redundancy in the event of a hardware failure or software corruption but that is very unlikely. We have proven upgrade process and we upgrade one firewall at a time to ensure there are no downtime.

Any failed upgrade has the potential to require Palo Alto assistance or RMA to recover but would be a loss of redundancy rather than an outage. This is proven upgrade process, so probability of issues is low.

Will reach out to Palo Alto TAC as needed. Monitoring of traffic through the firewalls' built-in diagnostics will validate that connections are not interrupted during this process

https://jira.maximus.com/browse/PDMSTECH-494
 
 NOTE that this is a special case deployment and testing effort for a single SSIS package.  Testing of interfaces to external vendors is only possible in the E2E environment, necessitating a best effort development task, review of the SSIS product in E2E, then implementing changes needed for a repeat cycle.  This SSIS package must be in place for testing on Monday 2/21/22 and it is possible additional changes will be needed as discovered.  Therefore an extended window is authorized,  implementation window ending Wednesday 2/23/22.
All changes will be attached to this Jira as artifacts, as well as promoted into the UAT branch for deployment. 
Edited deployment information boilerplate follows:
This  E2E deployment will include the SQL SSIS component "PMF File Processing" affecting the SSIS services only, and SQL scripts upon which it depends which will all be checked in to the UAT build branch.  For this deployment, only E2E will be deployed - subsequent to testing, UAT will be deployed under a separate CR.
These components will be tested by OH-PNM senior development and flagged as candidates for E2E builds in Jira. A development manager will then promotes them to the UAT branch in SVN. They are then compiled or executed against the OH-PNM INT02 environment by the Ohio Technical Operations team, and as is normal with non-public-facing SSIS packages, is not in scope for security scanning. Upon successful deployment, the objects are deployed into the E2E environment.
OHPNM_E2E schema does have PHI/PII data under CAB approval and Security exception requiring Production controls. 
Objects approved for deployment into the E2E environment by OH-PNM Business Analyst Testing Team will be logged in this Jira.  Business approval will be evidence that this review has occurred.
All SSIS script changes and SQL scripts it depends on will be checked into GIT under below branch
https://github.com/ohpnm/ohpnm-src/tree/UAT 
Affected CIs:
UORAXMMSQL01OHP - Database Microsoft SQL Server 2019: DBs OH_PNM_E2E, PDMS_EXL01, NPI
Version - Incremented during each deployment, to be referenced and tracked in comments in this Jira.
